post_text: Our school started the aviation program in 2019. We received word that we have been selected for a $8,000 grant to upgrade our flight simulator !!!
shared_text:
Oklahoma Aeronautics Commission Aviation Education
August 12 at 4:08 PM ·

Davenport Public Schools: The Commission approved an education grant for Davenport Public Schools “Flight School” program. The goal of the program is to familiarize students with policies and procedures related to the safe operation of aircraft and prepare them to pass the FAA Private Pilot computer-based knowledge exam, along with developing practical flight skills to log toward the Private Pilot flight training requirements. Davenport Public Schools has been approved to use the AOPA High School Aviation STEM 9th and 10th Grade Curriculum. It is estimated that 40 students will participate. The requested amount was $13,262.99; staff recommendation was for $8,000.

post_text: Davenport PS families please stay enrolled in Davenport schools. We have a virtual option and you will be able to stay with local teachers who love and know your children. Here is why it is so important. Oct 2 is our child count for state and federal funding. If our enrollment is down due to large number of students going to Epic we will not receive the funds. This could cut teachers, programs, or resources our school and community need. If you decide to come back at a later date for whatever reason, we may have huge class sizes, missing programs or lack resources. We have invested our time, energy, and hearts in your child. We want to see them grow and learn. Please talk with a teacher or administrator before jumping on the Epic bandwagon.
